<subSubSection id="C3776556ED0D3869FC9AFA30FC7DF99A" pageId="604" pageNumber="605" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0D3869FC9AFA30FC7DF99A" blockId="604.[810,1452,1329,2070]" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0D3869FC9AFA30FC25F9D9" bold="true" box="[863,992,1534,1560]" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0D3869FA44FA30FA69F9D6" box="[1409,1452,1534,1559]" italics="true" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">rect</emphasis>
(=straight), alluding to the linear body of the female of the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED0D386AFC9AF9ADFEBBFE74" lastPageId="607" lastPageNumber="608" pageId="604" pageNumber="605" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0D386BFC9AF9ADFE73F903" blockId="604.[810,1452,1329,2070]" lastBlockId="606.[136,778,1533,2070]" lastPageId="606" lastPageNumber="607" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0D3869FC9AF9ADFBA4F9BC" bold="true" box="[863,1121,1635,1661]" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">Descriptionoffemale</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0D3869FB7AF9ADFAF0F9BF" box="[1215,1333,1635,1662]" captionStart="FIGURE 408" captionStartId="605.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[208,1345,218,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-19@605.[205,1382,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="605" captionText="FIGURE 408. Scolecodes rectus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, ventral; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum and paragnaths; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592136/files/figure.png" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">Fig. 408A</figureCitation>
) elongate, cylindrical, straight, consisting of prosome and small unsegmented abdomen: bodylength 6.21 mm; maximum body width 0.86 mm in middle of prosome. Cephalosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0D3869FCF7F922FC60F8C7" box="[818,933,1772,1798]" captionStart="FIGURE 408" captionStartId="605.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[208,1345,218,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-19@605.[205,1382,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="605" captionText="FIGURE 408. Scolecodes rectus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, ventral; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum and paragnaths; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592136/files/figure.png" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">Fig. 408B</figureCitation>
) small, articulated from metasome, narrowing anteriorly. Metasome with 4 original pedigerous somites defined by incomplete dorsal sutures.Anteriorpart of body from rostrum tolevel of leg 4 occupying about 30% of total body length; legs 1–4 separated by equal intervals. Fourth pedigeroussomiteexpandedposteriorly, incorporatingfifth pedigerous somite and forming brood pouch. Copulatory pore positioned on posteroventral surface of incorporated genitalsomite. Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0D3869FB89F832FB7EF7D7" box="[1100,1211,2044,2070]" captionStart="FIGURE 408" captionStartId="605.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[208,1345,218,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-19@605.[205,1382,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="605" captionText="FIGURE 408. Scolecodes rectus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, ventral; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum and paragnaths; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592136/files/figure.png" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">Fig. 408C</figureCitation>
) small, unsegmented, longerthan wide (216×180 μm), not articulated from prosome, inserted into posteroventral surface of prosome. Caudal rami (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0F386BFEDAF98FFE54F99D" box="[287,401,1601,1628]" captionStart="FIGURE 408" captionStartId="605.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[208,1345,218,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-19@605.[205,1382,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="605" captionText="FIGURE 408. Scolecodes rectus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, ventral; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum and paragnaths; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592136/files/figure.png" pageId="606" pageNumber="607">Fig. 408D</figureCitation>
) about 2.8 times longerthan wide (125×45 μm), tapering in distal half, ornamented with scattered papillae: armed with 6 smallsetae (2 outer lateral plus 4 distal and subdistal).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF126655ED0C3868FF4DF8BDFD01F813" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592136" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4592136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592136/files/figure.png" pageId="605" pageNumber="606" startId="605.[136,245,1907,1933]" targetBox="[208,1345,218,1833]" targetPageId="605">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0C3868FF4DF8BDFD01F813" blockId="605.[136,1452,1907,2002]" pageId="605" pageNumber="606">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0C3868FF4DF8BDFEE8F84C" bold="true" box="[136,301,1907,1933]" pageId="605" pageNumber="606">FIGURE 408.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0C3868FEF0F8BAFE39F84C" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[309,508,1908,1934]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="605" pageNumber="606" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0C3868FEF0F8BAFE39F84C" box="[309,508,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="605" pageNumber="606">Scolecodes rectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED0C3868FDC1F8BAFD9AF84F" box="[516,607,1908,1934]" pageId="605" pageNumber="606" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0C3868FDC1F8BAFD9CF84F" bold="true" box="[516,601,1908,1934]" pageId="605" pageNumber="606">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, female. A, habitus, right; B, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, ventral; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum and paragnaths; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D–I, 0.02 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF126655ED0F386BFF4DFABBFEA8FA73" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592138" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4592138" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592138/files/figure.png" pageId="606" pageNumber="607" startId="606.[136,245,1397,1423]" targetBox="[159,1425,203,1341]" targetPageId="606">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0F386BFF4DFABBFEA8FA73" blockId="606.[136,1451,1397,1458]" pageId="606" pageNumber="607">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0F386BFF4DFABBFEE8FA51" bold="true" box="[136,301,1397,1424]" pageId="606" pageNumber="607">FIGURE 409.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0F386BFEF6FABBFE3CFA4E" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[307,505,1397,1423]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="606" pageNumber="607" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0F386BFEF6FABBFE3CFA4E" box="[307,505,1397,1423]" italics="true" pageId="606" pageNumber="607">Scolecodesrectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED0F386BFDC5FAB8FD9FFA51" box="[512,602,1398,1424]" pageId="606" pageNumber="607" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0F386BFDC5FAB8FD91FA51" bold="true" box="[512,596,1398,1424]" pageId="606" pageNumber="607">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, female. A, maxilla; B, leg 1; C, leg 2; D, leg 3; E, leg 4. Scale bars: A, 0.02 mm; B–E, 0.05 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0F386BFF78F904FE3DF835" blockId="606.[136,778,1533,2070]" pageId="606" pageNumber="607">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0F386BFEF6F907FE69F925" box="[307,428,1737,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 408" captionStartId="605.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[208,1345,218,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-19@605.[205,1382,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="605" captionText="FIGURE 408. Scolecodes rectus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, ventral; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum and paragnaths; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592136/files/figure.png" pageId="606" pageNumber="607">Fig. 408B</figureCitation>
) directed anteriorly, tapering. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0F386BFECFF925FEBEF8C7" box="[266,379,1771,1798]" captionStart="FIGURE 408" captionStartId="605.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[208,1345,218,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-19@605.[205,1382,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="605" captionText="FIGURE 408. Scolecodes rectus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, ventral; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum and paragnaths; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592136/files/figure.png" pageId="606" pageNumber="607">Fig. 408C</figureCitation>
) unsegmented, consistingof greatly expanded, globular proximal part and narrow, digitiform distal part; armed with 4 setae on proximal part and about 8 setaeon distal part. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0F386BFE37F89CFDA6F8AD" box="[498,611,1874,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 408" captionStartId="605.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[208,1345,218,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-19@605.[205,1382,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="605" captionText="FIGURE 408. Scolecodes rectus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, ventral; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum and paragnaths; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592136/files/figure.png" pageId="606" pageNumber="607">Fig. 408F</figureCitation>
) 3-segmented, consistingof short coxa, broad basis, and unsegmented endopod; basis slightly longerthan wide; endopod tapering, terminating in claw and bearing 1 outer and 4 inner smallsetae at base of claw.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0F386BFF78F832FB1DF8E6" blockId="606.[136,778,1533,2070]" lastBlockId="606.[810,1452,1533,2070]" pageId="606" pageNumber="607">
Labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0F386BFEEDF832FE58F7D7" box="[296,413,2044,2070]" captionStart="FIGURE 408" captionStartId="605.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[208,1345,218,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-19@605.[205,1382,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="605" captionText="FIGURE 408. Scolecodes rectus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, ventral; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum and paragnaths; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592136/files/figure.png" pageId="606" pageNumber="607">Fig. 408G</figureCitation>
) simple, with slightly produced mid-region of free posterior margin. Mandible with coxa represented by setulose lobe (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0F386BFB41F9D1FB3AF9FB" box="[1156,1279,1567,1594]" captionStart="FIGURE 408" captionStartId="605.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[208,1345,218,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-19@605.[205,1382,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="605" captionText="FIGURE 408. Scolecodes rectus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, ventral; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum and paragnaths; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592136/files/figure.png" pageId="606" pageNumber="607">Fig. 408G</figureCitation>
); palp forming rectangular lobe (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0F386BFC34F98FFBA2F99D" box="[1009,1127,1601,1628]" captionStart="FIGURE 408" captionStartId="605.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[208,1345,218,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-19@605.[205,1382,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="605" captionText="FIGURE 408. Scolecodes rectus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, ventral; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum and paragnaths; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592136/files/figure.png" pageId="606" pageNumber="607">Fig. 408H</figureCitation>
) bearing 3 large naked setae distally on medial margin and 3 small pinnate setae plus 1 pointed, setiform process on distal margin. Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0F386BFCF7F969FC58F903" box="[818,925,1703,1730]" captionStart="FIGURE 408" captionStartId="605.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[208,1345,218,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-19@605.[205,1382,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="605" captionText="FIGURE 408. Scolecodes rectus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, ventral; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum and paragnaths; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592136/files/figure.png" pageId="606" pageNumber="607">Fig. 408I</figureCitation>
) lobate, bearing 7 pinnate setae (3 large setae on medial margin and 4 smaller, apical or subapical setae). Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0F386BFC54F925FBC3F8C7" box="[913,1030,1771,1798]" captionStart="FIGURE 408" captionStartId="605.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[208,1345,218,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-19@605.[205,1382,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="605" captionText="FIGURE 408. Scolecodes rectus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, ventral; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum and paragnaths; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592136/files/figure.png" pageId="606" pageNumber="607">Fig. 408A</figureCitation>
) lobate, unsegmented, armed distally with 3 naked setae. Maxilliped absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0F386BFC9AF8FEFC61F7D7" blockId="606.[810,1452,1533,2070]" pageId="606" pageNumber="607">
Legs 1–4 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0F386BFC1BF8FEFB84F88B" box="[990,1089,1840,1866]" captionStart="FIGURE 409" captionStartId="606.[136,245,1397,1423]" captionTargetBox="[159,1425,203,1341]" captionTargetId="figure-21@606.[136,1451,184,1371]" captionTargetPageId="606" captionText="FIGURE 409. Scolecodes rectus sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, leg 1; C, leg 2; D, leg 3; E, leg 4. Scale bars: A, 0.02 mm; B–E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592138" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592138/files/figure.png" pageId="606" pageNumber="607">Fig. 409</figureCitation>
B-E) biramous, each consisting of unsegmented protopod, 2-segmented exopod and 1- segmented endopod. Protopods armed with outer seta (derived from basis) only. Both rami obscurely defined from protopod; all setae naked, most spiniform, short but thick, with nipple-like tip. Armature formula for legs 1–4 as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0E386AFF2DFF63FEF2FEB0" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">
