</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0E386AFF78FE55FEBBFE74" blockId="607.[136,778,411,846]" box="[189,382,411,438]" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFF78FE55FF3FFE74" bold="true" box="[189,250,411,437]" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED0E386AFF78FE73FD84FC8F" pageId="607" pageNumber="608" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0E386AFF78FE73FD84FC8F" blockId="607.[136,778,411,846]" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFF78FE73FEEFFE16" bold="true" box="[189,298,445,471]" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0E386AFE84FE73FDCAFE16" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[321,527,445,471]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="607" pageNumber="608" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFE84FE73FDCAFE16" box="[321,527,445,471]" italics="true" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">Scolecodes rectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED0E386AFDDAFE73FD46FE19" box="[543,643,445,472]" pageId="607" pageNumber="608" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFDDAFE73FDB9FE16" bold="true" box="[543,636,445,471]" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
shares the possession of 2-segmented exopods on legs 1–4 only with 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0E386AFF4DFDCFFED2FDDA" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[136,279,513,540]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="607" pageNumber="608" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugetensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFF4DFDCFFF53FDDA" box="[136,150,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFF64FDCCFED2FDDA" box="[161,279,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">pugetensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED0E386AFED9FDCFFEB1FDDD" box="[284,372,513,540]" pageId="607" pageNumber="608" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFED9FDCFFEABFDDA" bold="true" box="[284,366,513,539]" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Thischaracterstate distinguishesthe new species from the 
<typeStatus id="54D6887FED0E386AFEBCFDEAFE6CFDFF" box="[377,425,548,574]" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0E386AFDC8FDEDFD58FDFC" authorityName="Henderson" authorityYear="1931" box="[525,669,547,573]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecimorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="607" pageNumber="608" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huntsmani">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFDC8FDEDFD58FDFC" box="[525,669,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">S. huntsmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0E386AFF0CFD8BFE9BFD9E" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[201,350,581,608]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="607" pageNumber="608" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugetensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFF0CFD8BFF12FD9E" box="[201,215,581,607]" italics="true" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFF2DFD88FE9BFD9E" box="[232,350,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">pugetensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED0E386AFEACFD8BFE02FDA1" box="[361,455,581,608]" pageId="607" pageNumber="608" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFEACFD8BFE04FD9E" bold="true" box="[361,449,581,607]" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
as follows: the abdomen is longer than wide (vs. as long as wide in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0E386AFD8BFDA9FD24FD40" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[590,737,615,642]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="607" pageNumber="608" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugetensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFD8BFDA9FD99FD40" box="[590,604,615,641]" italics="true" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFDAEFDA6FD24FD40" box="[619,737,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">pugetensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED0E386AFD2DFDA9FF7CFD65" pageId="607" pageNumber="608" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFD2DFDA9FF71FD62" bold="true" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
), the mandible carries a setiform apical process in addition to 6 setae (vs. no setiform process in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0E386AFDBCFD62FCCCFD04" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[633,777,684,710]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="607" pageNumber="608" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugetensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFDBCFD62FD42FD07" box="[633,647,684,710]" italics="true" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFD56FD62FCCCFD04" box="[659,777,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">pugetensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED0E386AFF4DFD03FF27FD29" box="[136,226,717,744]" pageId="607" pageNumber="608" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFF4DFD03FF18FD26" bold="true" box="[136,221,717,743]" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
), the maxillule is armed with 7 setae (vs. 6 setae in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0E386AFF6CFD3EFEFAFCC8" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[169,319,752,778]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="607" pageNumber="608" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugetensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFF6CFD3EFF72FCCB" box="[169,183,752,778]" italics="true" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFF0CFD3EFEFAFCC8" box="[201,319,752,777]" italics="true" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">pugetensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED0E386AFE8FFD21FE62FCCB" box="[330,423,751,778]" pageId="607" pageNumber="608" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFE8FFD21FE67FCC8" bold="true" box="[330,418,751,777]" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
), the maxilla is armed with 3 setae (vs. 4 setae in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0E386AFEA8FCDCFDC5FCEA" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[365,512,786,812]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="607" pageNumber="608" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugetensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFEA8FCDCFEBEFCED" box="[365,379,786,812]" italics="true" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFE4FFCDCFDC5FCEA" box="[394,512,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">pugetensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED0E386AFDCDFCDFFDA7FCED" box="[520,610,785,812]" pageId="607" pageNumber="608" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0E386AFDCDFCDFFD98FCEA" bold="true" box="[520,605,785,811]" pageId="607" pageNumber="608">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
), and the rami of legs 1–4 are armed with fewer setae.
</paragraph>
